in-class HCM platforms. In the course of your project work and our development programs, you\u2019ll acquire the research, client relations, problem solving, presentation, project management, and information technology skills that are foundational to successful software and technical consulting careers. Cloud Technology Applications: ArcLight offers the unique opportunity for candidates to learn and implement Oracle\u2019s innovative new product, the HCM Cloud. Oracle\u2019s HCM offerings support Benefits Management, Compensation Management, Payroll Processing, Talent Management and other essential elements of strategic human resources management. Oracle\u2019s Cloud offerings leverage the technologies accelerating modern business including Big Data Analytics, AI, Blockchain and others. Analytical Capabilities: Throughout the implementation cycle for HCM deployments, ArcLight consultants are challenged to break down and clarify difficult concepts for customers and \u2018dig in\u2019 and build out Oracle\u2019s Cloud modules. As you design, test and implement Oracle\u2019s Cloud solutions, considerations of the potential downstream impacts of decisions ensure the capabilities you\u2019ve designed and delivered are robust, sustainable, and readily adaptable to future needs. Process Improvement: Work with peers to continuously improve ArcLight\u2019s delivery methodologies and tools. Contribute to enhancing ArcLight\u2019s value proposition for clients through process efficiencies, design excellence, quality assurance and deep functional and technical knowledge. Career Advancement: As you master Oracle Cloud technologies and gain experience and insights with the client needs ArcLight addresses, opportunities to advance in technical roles as well as client-facing consultative, project management, and customer support career tracks will open up for you and enable your continued professional and technical career growth. Benefits: Competitive compensation structure (top of market) Quarterly / Annual bonus program rewarding individual efforts and company progress Medical, Dental, Vision coverage 401(k) retirement plan Life insurance benefits Cell Phone and internet reimbursement Charitable contribution program Flex-time off program Floating holidays / Company holidays Qualifications: 0-2 years of experience Demonstrated analytical abilities. Willing to learn a range of business or technical specialties based on business needs. Excellent interpersonal, communication and presentation skills Demonstrated ability to convey complex information in a clear and concise manner Strong academic performance. Intermediate to expert-level Excel skills. Access experience a plus. English fluency (written and verbal) required. Technical foundation in software development languages and methodologies (e.g. Java, PL/SQL, etc.). Any experience with Oracle is a plus. Software development experience with SQL, PL/SQL and Web Services is desirable. Requirements: Bachelor\u2019s degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, Finance, Economics, Statistics, Business, Human Resources or related field, or its equivalent. Willing to travel 50% of the time. This position is not eligible for visa sponsorship. About ArcLight Consulting ArcLight Consulting is a leading consultancy specializing in Oracle\u2019s Cloud technologies. Our expertise with the HCM and ERP Cloud suites has led us to become a premier partner for Oracle. ArcLight Consulting is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability and protected veterans status or any other characteristic protected by law. ", 
